Defendant in custody.
The Court comments and sentences the defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of seventy-four (74) months.  That is forty-four (44) months initial confinement followed by thirty (30) months extended supervision, on each count, concurrent.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) maintain absolute sobriety;
5) have no contact with Richard and Sebastiana Novak;
6) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
7) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search or combination;
8) Any lectures, speeches and speaking with others about the effects of drugs to be done by the defendant is at the agents discretion.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  
The Court also finds the defendant eligible for the Substance Abuse Program, but only after first serving 12 months of initial confinement.
The defendant has credit for 506 days.
The Court orders a civil judgment of restitution for the balance which is still owing.  State to draft judgment.
